    <bioghist>1977 speaker series sponsored by the University of Michigan featuring film critics, screenwriters, producers, directors, and production staff commenting on aspects of Altman's films; Robert Altman presentation concluded the series.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Taped presentations include Robert Altman, Andrew Sarris with a film critic's view of Altman, Molly Haskell on the role of women in Altman's films, Joan Tewksbury on the role of screenwriter, Alan Rudolph on the role of a director, and producer Tommy Thompson and Elaine Bradish, Altman's office manager, discussing working with Altman.</scopecontent>
